@DATABASE "pnmpaste.guide"
@INDEX "ImageEditor.guide/INDEX"
@FONT helvetica.font 13
@SMARTWRAP

@NODE MAIN "ImageEditor - Operator: Paste [pnmpaste]"
@TOC "Operator.guide/MAIN"

@{LINDENT 4}
@{PAR}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{B}Paste@{UB}@{FG TEXT}@{LINE}
@{PAR}@{B}Paste a rectangle into a portable anymap.@{UB}@{LINE}
@{PAR}Reads two portable anymaps as input. Inserts the paste image into the workfile at the specified location,
and produces a portable anymap the same size as the workfile as output.@{LINE}
@{PAR}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}This tool is most useful in combination with @{" Cut " LINK "pnmcut.guide/MAIN"}. For instance,
if you want to edit a small segment of a large image, and your image editor cannot edit the large image,
you can cut out the segment you are interested in, edit it, and then paste it back in.@{FG TEXT}@{LINE}
@{PAR}The option specifies the operation to use when doing the paste.
The default is replace. The other, logical operations are only allowed if both input images are bitmaps.
These operations act as if white is TRUE and black is FALSE.@{LINE}
@{PAR}See also @{" Cut " LINK "pnmcut.guide/MAIN"} and @{" Arithmetic " LINK "pnmarith.guide/MAIN"}.@{LINE}
@{PAR}[@{B}pnmpaste@{UB}] @{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{I}Copyright (C) 1991 by Jef Poskanzer @{UI}@{FG TEXT}@{LINE}

@ENDNODE
